@gunan: 

So I got it working half way until I hit this error upon the command `import tensorflow as tf`

`  import numpy as np
  File "C:\Program Files\Anaconda3\lib\site-packages\numpy\__init__.py", line 142, in <module>
    from . import add_newdocs

    from numpy.lib import add_newdoc
  File "C:\Program Files\Anaconda3\lib\site-packages\numpy\lib\__init__.py", line 8, in <module>
    from .type_check import *
  File "C:\Program Files\Anaconda3\lib\site-packages\numpy\lib\type_check.py", line 11, in <module>
    import numpy.core.numeric as _nx
  File "C:\Program Files\Anaconda3\lib\site-packages\numpy\core\__init__.py", line 26, in <module>
    raise ImportError(msg)

Importing the multiarray numpy extension module failed.  Most
likely you are trying to import a failed build of numpy.

Original error was: DLL load failed: The specified procedure could not be found.`

I tried reinstalling numpy but still got more errors. Thoughts? Is this an Anaconda related error?
